SYNOPSIS
========
   float pow(int|float base, int|float exp)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   The function returns the value of base(E) raised to the power of exp(E).

   USAGE
   =====
         pow(-2, 3)      // returns -8.0
         pow(8, 1.0/3.0) // returns 2.0

HISTORY
=======
   - introduced (3.2.7)
   - changed (3.2.9) -- added integers as arguments.

SEE ALSO
========
   exp(E), log(E)
